{[%evp 0,59,30,20,20,15,15,7,7,16,16,16,3,5,5,5,15,5,43,13,33,40,48,22,69,48,
37,47,55,39,43,23,21,29,45,57,91,91,70,73,100,88,107,102,113,104,137,130,136,
127,138,105,126,95,213,168,165,112,100,114,120,143]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3
Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. Bd3 d5 8. exd5 O-O 9. O-O Bg4 {
This move becomes quite popular several years ago. Black is trying to solve
his problems by force. He temporary sacrifices two pawns. In the begining
Black was very successfull with this approach, but later White find some
interesting resources which put some questions of Black's strategy.} 10. f3 {
this is the most principled reply} (10. Be2 {Magnus tried this move, but Black
successfully solves his problems after} Bxe2 11. Nxe2 cxd5 12. Bg5 Be7 (12...
c6) 13. Nd4 Qd7 14. Qd3 Rfe8 15. Rad1 Ne4 {1/2-1/2 (45) Carlsen,M (2861)
-Nakamura,H (2761) Abidjan 2019}) 10... Bh5 {Here White has a choice how to
win the second pawn. I believe that both continuations gives White slightly
better chances, the arising positions are close to equal, but White can push
without risk} 11. Bg5 {Logical move, White is finishing the development} (11.
dxc6 {This is the most direkt try, White is taking the second pawn immediately.
Black will need some time to take the pawns back and White can coordinate his
pieces and put some pressure.} Qd4+ 12. Kh1 Bxc3 13. bxc3 Qxc3 14. Bf4 $1 {
I believe that this move is the best try for White to fight for an advantage} (
14. Rb1 {This is the old mainline, which also leads to a slightly better
position.} Bg6 15. Rb3 Qxc6 16. Bb2 Rfd8 17. Qa1 $14 {1-0 (32) Xiong,J (2709)
-Oparin,G (2652) Lichess.org INT 2020 It is close to a draw, but White is the
one who is pressing}) 14... Qxc6 15. Qe2 a6 16. Qe5 Ra7 17. Be3 Raa8 18. Qc5
Qxc5 19. Bxc5 {1-0 (47) Paravyan,D (2639)-Deac,B (2605) Riga 2021 and Black
failed to defend this unpleasant endgame}) 11... Qd6 (11... cxd5 {This line is
probably good for Black, but he needs to find too many only moves to maintain
the ballance} 12. Bxf6 Qxf6 13. Nxd5 Qxb2 14. Rb1 Bc5+ 15. Kh1 Qe5 16. f4 Bxd1
17. fxe5 Bg4 18. Nxc7 {Everything is almost forced until here} Rac8 19. Rb7 Bd7
$2 (19... Rfd8 {was better but after:} 20. e6 fxe6 21. Bc4 {White is still
pressing} Bf5) 20. Na6 Be6 21. Nxc5 Rxc5 22. Rxa7 $16 {1-0 (34) Hovhannisyan,R
(2669)-Neiksans,A (2560) Riga 2021}) (11... Bxc3 12. bxc3 cxd5 13. Re1 c6 14.
Qd2 Bg6 15. Bf1 $14) 12. Bxf6 Qxf6 13. Ne4 (13. dxc6 Bxc3 14. bxc3 Qxc3 15. Be4
Bg6 16. Qd7 Rad8 17. Qxc7 Qc5+ 18. Kh1 Bxe4 19. fxe4 Rc8 20. Qd7 Qxc6 21. Qxa7
Qxe4 22. Rfe1 Qxc2 $11 {1/2-1/2 (41) Nepomniachtchi,I (2774)-Caruana,F (2842)
Ekaterinburg 2021}) 13... Qxb2 14. dxc6 Bg6 15. Kh1 Qd4 16. Qe2 Rfe8 17. Rad1
Qe5 18. Bc4 Rad8 19. Rd7 $16 Rxd7 20. cxd7 Rd8 21. Rd1 Kf8 22. c3 Ba3 23. Rd5
Qe7 24. Bb5 Bd6 25. c4 a6 26. Ba4 Bxe4 27. Qxe4 Qxe4 28. fxe4 f6 29. Ra5 Rb8
30. g3 {1-0 (30) Yu,Y (2738)-Mamedyarov,S (2774) Stavanger 2019 CBM 191 [Yu,
Yangyi]} *

