{[%evp 0,80,20,15,11,7,16,7,9,3,3,3,5,3,3,3,3,5,5,-5,-7,2,-2,-7,6,-12,11,-34,
-28,-24,-23,-30,-6,-1,21,0,0,-17,-24,-8,0,-9,-7,-8,5,27,27,4,25,22,32,37,16,1,
13,24,30,12,0,-13,-20,-23,-28,-106,-102,-99,-117,-108,-82,-94,-46,-48,-14,0,
-44,-46,15,-131,-131,-131,-58,-113,-102]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4
exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. Bd3 d5 8. exd5 cxd5 9. O-O O-O 10. h3 (10. Bg5
{is the old main line} c6 11. Qf3 Bd6) 10... c6 11. Qf3 Re8 12. Bg5 h6 {
This is an interesting approach. The rule is that Black is not worried about
the double f-pawns if the queens are exchanged. But things are far from easy.
White has a simple plan to maneuver the knight to e2 and then push c4 at an
appropriate moment. The other idea is to occupy the f5-square and  reach an
endgame with a knight against a dark-squared bishop. In this game Caruana
provokes the exchange by playing h6 and at end it worked well, but during the
game Morozevich missed several chances to obtains a better position.} (12...
Bd6) 13. Bxf6 Qxf6 14. Qxf6 gxf6 15. Ne2 $1 Bd6 (15... c5 {was tried by Navara,
but he also didn't equalize completely} 16. c3 Ba5 17. Nf4 c4 {Navara fixes
the b2-pawn, but I am not sure this is a good decision. Now the d5-pawn is
weak and also the d4-square.} 18. Bc2 Re5 19. Rfd1 Rb8 20. Rab1 Be6 21. Kf1 Kf8
22. Ne2 Bb6 23. Nd4 $14 {0-1 (62) Morozevich,A (2731)-Navara,D (2722) Bilbao
2014 Black even won that game, but I think that White won the opening battle.})
16. Rad1 Be6 17. Ng3 Rab8 18. Nh5 {The other nasty idea, which you need to
remember. It is not easy for Black to defend the f6-pawn.} Be5 19. b3 Kf8 20.
f4 Bb2 21. Rf3 c5 22. Bh7 Rb6 23. c3 $2 (23. Kh2 {This the prophylactic move
poses serious problems for Black} c4 24. bxc4 dxc4 25. c3 {[%cal Rf4f5,Rh5f6,
Rf3g3] White has a lot of threats for example:} Ra6 $4 26. f5 Bc8 27. Rg3)
23... Bc8 $2 (23... d4 $1 24. Nxf6 Bf5 {and if} 25. Nxe8 $4 (25. Bxf5 Rxf6 26.
Bb1 $11) 25... Bxh7 $19) 24. Rg3 d4 25. cxd4 $4 (25. Rg8+ $1 {Morozevich
misses a clear win after:} Ke7 26. Re1+ Re6 27. Rxe8+ Kxe8 28. Ng7+ Ke7 29.
Nxe6 Bxc3 30. Re2 Bxe6 31. Bd3 $18) 25... Bxd4+ 26. Kh2 Bd7 27. Rg8+ Ke7 28.
Re1+ Re6 29. Rxe6+ fxe6 30. Rg7+ Kd6 $11 31. Rg6 Rh8 32. Rxh6 Bb5 33. g4 Bd3
34. f5 Be5+ 35. Kg2 Be4+ 36. Kf2 Bd4+ 37. Ke2 c4 38. g5 c3 39. Ng3 c2 40. Nxe4+
Ke5 *

