h4 d6 {Looks very logical to face a flank attack by a counter in the centre.}
9. c4 Nb6 (9... Ba6 10. exd6 cxd6 11. Qxe7+ Nxe7 12. Nc3 {Black has no play
against white's better structure}) 10. exd6 {As we can no longer hold on to
the e5-pawn, we release the tension and aim for a slightly better endgame.}
cxd6 (10... Qxe2+ 11. Bxe2 cxd6 (11... Bxd6 {leaves doubled pawns on the
c-file unattended and after} 12. Nc3 O-O (12... Be6 13. b3 {Supporting the
c4-pawn.} O-O-O 14. Bb2 $14 {[%cal Ge1c1]}) 13. Be3 {[%cal Gc4c5]} Bb4 14. Rc1
Be6 15. b3 $14) 12. Bf3 Bb7 13. b3 O-O-O 14. Nd2 $14 d5 15. O-O) 11. Be3 {
Avoiding the queen exchange as if 11.Qxe7 Bxe7 Black is in time to neutralize
the position with .. .Be6 and d5 next.} d5 {Trying to challenge the center
immediately.} (11... Be6 12. Qc2 {[%cal Gb1d2,Gf1d3]}) 12. Nd2 dxc4 (12... Be6
13. c5 Nd7 14. Nb3 $14) 13. g3 Be6 (13... Nd5 14. Bg2 Bb7 15. Qxc4 $16 Nxe3 16.
Bxc6+) 14. Bg2 Qc7 (14... Bd5 15. O-O $14) 15. h5 $1 {A new move which is of
course the top move of the engine.} h6 16. Bh3 Qd7 17. Bxe6 Qxe6 18. Rh4 {
The point of h4-h5} Bb4 19. O-O-O (19. Bxb6 Bxd2+ 20. Kxd2 Qxe2+ 21. Kxe2 axb6
22. Rxc4) 19... O-O 20. Re4 Qf5 21. Qg4 Qh7 $1 {Not an easy move to pay OTB} (
21... Qxg4 22. Rxg4 {Threatening Bxh6.} f5 23. Rg6 {With the double attack of
Rxc6 and Bxh6.}) 22. Rf4 $36 {[%cal Gd2c4]} *

