Nezar,M (2396) -Szabo,K (2545) Haguenau 2013}) (10. Nb5 Nxe4 $1 (10... dxe3 {
Interesting idea. Black has full compensation for the queen's sacrifice.} 11.
Rxd8 Rxd8 12. f3 Be6 13. Qe1 a5 $44 {Li,R (2426)-Avrukh,B (2609) Chicago 2015})
11. N5xd4 (11. N3xd4 Nb4 {This is the suggestion of the computer. Both sides
must be careful.} 12. f3 (12. Ne6 {0-1 (42) Sinyanskiy,M (2042) -Ambartsumova,
K (2307) Kazan 2016} Bxe3+ 13. fxe3 Nxa2+ 14. Kb1 Bxe6 15. Rxd8 Raxd8 $19)
12... Nf6 $15) 11... Nb4 12. Kb1 Nd5 $15 {An excellent decision. Now, the
c3-square is getting vulnerable.}) 10... h6 11. Bh4 Re8) (6. a4 a6 7. Nc3 Nf6
$1 (7... Nge7 8. Nd5 $1 {see 5. a4 move order: 1-0 (20) Esipenko,A (2720)
-Dudin,G (2434) Struga 2021} (8. Be2 O-O 9. O-O d6 $13 {games})) 8. Bd3 (8. Nd5
O-O $1 $15) 8... d6 $11 {There are many games in this position. Black is fine
here.}) 6... Nf6 (6... Nd4 7. Nxd4 Bxd4 8. c3 (8. Nc3 $5 $146 Bxc3+ (8... d6 9.
Bd2 $14 {There is no problem for Black.}) 9. bxc3 {As often happens in Scotch,
the doubled pawns provide new opportunities for the dark-squared bishop. Now,
Black should reckon with Ba3.} d6 (9... Ne7 10. c4 O-O 11. Bb2 d6 12. O-O-O
$132) 10. Qb5+ c6 11. Qg5 $11) 8... Bb6 9. Be3 {Maybe this is the most
principled choice. White wants to solve the problems with the f2-square and
the development of their pieces.} (9. Na3 Ne7 (9... a6 $14) 10. Nc4 (10. g3 O-O
11. Bg2 d5 12. O-O Re8 13. Rd1 Bd7 14. Be3 Bxe3 15. Qxe3 c6 $14) 10... O-O 11.
Qc2 d5 12. Nxb6 axb6 13. Bd3 dxe4 14. Bxe4 $11 f5 {The best save.} 15. Bd3 Ng6
16. O-O f4 17. f3 Ra5 $13 {Black's Rook is ready to attack.}) (9. a4 $5 $146 a6
(9... a5 10. Na3 $14) 10. a5 Ba7 11. Be3 $14) 9... Nf6 10. Bxb6 axb6 11. c4 O-O
12. Nc3 b5 $1 $146 {Good idea! Black wants to open the position, because
White's king is still in the centre.} (12... Nxe4 13. Nxe4 f5 $13 14. Nd6 cxd6
{Terrible pawn structure for Black. He has nothing in return. All the endgames
are winning for White.} 15. Qd2 $14) (12... Re8 13. f3 {In this Maroczy type
of structure, Black's only counterplay is based on the advance ...d7-d5.
Nevertheless, he has no time for that.} c6 14. O-O-O d5 15. cxd5 cxd5 16. Qc2
$16 {with an obvious advantage for White.}) 13. cxb5 d5 14. O-O-O c6 $44 {
Dangerous for White.}) (6... a5 7. a4 Nf6 (7... d6) 8. Be3 ({After} 8. Nc3 {
the position will transpose to the main line in current game.} O-O {ctr f7})
8... Bxe3 9. Qxe3 Nb4 {and now White's best move is the awkward} 10. Na3 {
after which is clear that he is not fighting for an advantage anymore. Black
can simply castle and start preparing d7-d5 break.}) (6... d6 {This is very
passive.} 7. Nc3 Nf6 (7... Nge7 8. Be3 {ctr f7}) 8. Be3 $14) (6... Nge7 7. Nc3
O-O 8. Be3 f5 {A thematic idea in such positions. Black wants to create
outpost on e5-square with ...f5-f4.} 9. exf5 $1 (9. O-O-O fxe4 10. Nxe4 d5 11.
Nc3 Kh8 $13 {Prophylactic from checks. 0-1 (32) Chigaev,M (2644) -Grandelius,N
(2691) Douglas 2019}) 9... Bxe3 10. Qxe3 Nxf5 11. Qd2 Qe8+ 12. Be2 d6 13. O-O-O
Be6 14. f4 $16 {1-0 (78) Vallejo Pons,F (2678)-Sosa,T (2508) Linares 2019}) (
6... Qf6 7. a4 $1 (7. Nc3 Nge7 {transposes.}) 7... a6 (7... a5 8. Nc3 Nb4 (8...
Nge7 9. Be3 Bxe3 10. Qxe3 O-O 11. O-O-O $14 {promising line for White}) 9. Nb5
$1 Ne7 10. c3 Na6 11. e5 $1 $146 Qg6 12. h4 $16 {Black's queen is in trouble.})
8. Nc3 Nge7 9. Nd5 $1 Nxd5 10. exd5+ Ne7 11. h4 (11. a5 Ba7 $5 12. h4 {White
has a serious space advantage. The idea is Bg5.} d6 $2 13. Ra4 Bf5 14. g4 {
Total domination for White!} Bg6 15. h5 Qxf2+ 16. Qxf2 Bxf2+ 17. Kd1 $18 {
1-0 (42) Khamrakulov,D (2477)-Yargici,M (1913) Konya 2017} (17. Kxf2 $18))
11... h6 (11... Qd6 $5) 12. Bd2 $1 O-O (12... Qxb2 13. Rh3 Qxc2 14. a5 Ba7 15.
Rc1 $44 {dangerous line for Black}) 13. a5 Ba7 14. Bc3 Qd6 15. O-O-O Nxd5 16.
Rxd5 {Now White's attack is unstoppable.} Qxd5 17. Qg4 g6 18. Qf4 Kh7 19. Bd3
$16 f5 20. Bd2 $18 {1-0 (20) Esipenko,A (2720)-Dudin,G (2434) Struga 2021}) 7.
e5 Nd5 8. c4 Ndb4 9. c5 Bxc5 10. Nxc5 (10. a3 Na6 11. Qg4 Bf8 12. Nc3 d5 {
Without compensation for White.} 13. Qg3 Be6 {Solid for Black.} 14. Bf4 Qd7 15.
Rc1 h5 $15 16. Bxa6 bxa6 17. O-O $17 {1/2 (30)-1/2 (30) Mislin,R-Goehring,D
freechess.de 2019}) 10... Nd4 11. Qg4 $1 $13 {This is the computer's
suggestion. The position is very unclear.} (11. Qe4 Qe7 $1 12. Na3 Qxc5 13. Bc4
Ndc6 $15 {0-1 (30) Keso,E (2301)-Nyysti,S (2336) Helsinki 2020}) 11... Ndc2+
12. Ke2 O-O 13. Bh6 g6 14. Na3 d6 15. Qc4 Nxa1 16. Ne4 c5 17. Bg5 Be6 18. Qc1
Qb6 19. Bf6 Nc6 20. f3 Nd4+ 21. Ke1 Bd5 22. Nxd6 Rfd8 23. Nac4 Qb4+ 24. Kf2 b5
