{[%evp 0,27,35,18,14,16,28,-4,-4,-4,103,75,56,52,107,62,61,58,68,66,61,24,24,
52,61,68,63,45,68,68]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 {[%cal Bd8h4,
Bg7g6,Bf8e7,Bc6d4] Now, we are going to examine all sidelines with the
exception of 4...Qf6 and 4...Qh4.} g6 (4... d5 {has never been tried at GM
level, but is quite popular at an amateur level. Black directly attempts to
strike in the centre, though the opening of the position should favour the
side having a lead in development (White). White has a couple of promising
options, but I think that} 5. Nxc6 $5 {is the easiest choice.} (5. Bb5 $5) 5...
bxc6 6. exd5 Qxd5 {[%cal Bd1e2,Bb1c3,Bc1e3]} (6... cxd5 7. Bb5+ {and Black
either loses a pawn or the right to castle.}) 7. Bd3 $5 (7. Qe2+ Qe6 8. Nc3
