comments to the previous chapter, the e4-pawn gives White a stable static
advantage due to the better central control. Therefore, White's priority is to
stabilize the position and complete the development. Besides the normal
developing moves such as Be2, 0-0, and Nc3, the aggressive Bg5 is always on
the agenda. The idea of playing Bg5 is one of the main points behind Nf3.} ({
