{one of the best lines for..black! ...Nd4! without the inclusion of 8...a5 9.
a4 moves !} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Bc5 5. Nb3 Bb6 6. Nc3 Nf6 7.
Qe2 O-O (7... d6 {This is a mistake.} 8. Be3 {and White is better.}) 8. Bg5 {
[%cal Gc3d5] Previously, we saw h6 Bh4 and a5 a4 and then Nd4.} Nd4 $1 {
Actually, this is a very interesting possibility for Black.} 9. Qd2 {This is
the best move you need to know.} Nxb3 10. axb3 Re8 11. O-O-O {White can castle
long.} ({But even} 11. f3 $5 {is interesting. White is slightly better. Maybe
we are threatening a move like Nd5.} h6 {This is the correct move to play. Now
Bxf6 Qxf6 and Nd5 would have been good strategically, but tactically it is
flawed because b2 is dropping.} 12. Be3 Bxe3 13. Qxe3 {Yes, the only question
here is whether d5 can be played.} d5 $1 {Indeed, this is the best move.} (
13... d6 $2 {one mistake like this..and its..almost game over again !!} 14.
O-O-O {White is once again better. White is also helped by the hook on h6
which will speed up our attack.} Bd7 15. g4 $18 {[%cal Gg4g5] maybe even g5
directly which forces the opening of the g-line.} Qe7 ({For example,} 15... a5
{here after} 16. Bc4 $18 {the computer says that White is totally winning.} ({
Even after} 16. Kb1 a4 17. bxa4 Bxa4 18. Nxa4 ({Maybe even} 18. Bc4 {would
have been good enough.}) ({Maybe even} 18. g5 hxg5 19. Qxg5 {White is
obviously much faster.}) 18... Rxa4 19. Bb5 {is winning by force.}) 16... a4
17. bxa4 Bxa4 18. Nxa4 Rxa4 19. Bxf7+) 16. h4 Bc6 17. g5 $18) {Again, White
has chances for a small advantage:} 14. O-O-O c6 15. g4 {I briefly analyzed
this g4 move with the g5 idea and now some idea with Qb6 or Qa5 or something.}
Qb6 (15... Qa5 16. g5 $36) (15... Qc7 16. g5 $36) 16. Qxb6 axb6 {It is almost
equal.} 17. exd5 Ra1+ 18. Kd2 Rxd1+ 19. Kxd1 Rd8 20. Bd3 Nxd5 21. Nxd5 Rxd5 22.
Ke2 $14 {[%cal Gh1a1] Indeed, the best moves were played. We have a small
advantage here, according to the computer, intending Ra1. But what can you do?
If both players play the best moves, you will have a more or less equal game.
But believe me, you will hardly ever get this position after 20 moves with
both players playing like a computer.}) 11... h6 $1 12. Bxf6 Qxf6 13. f3 $2 Ba5
(13... c6 $3 $17 14. Bd3 d5) 14. Kb1 d6 15. Nd5 Bxd2 16. Nxf6+ gxf6 17. Rxd2 f5
18. Bd3 fxe4 19. Bxe4 Rb8 20. g4 Be6 21. g5 hxg5 22. Rg1 Kg7 23. Rxg5+ Kf6 24.
Ra5 a6 25. h4 Rh8 26. Rh2 d5 27. Bd3 Rh5 28. Ra4 Rbh8 29. Kc1 c5 30. Ra5 b5 31.
Rxa6 c4 32. bxc4 bxc4 33. Be2 Rxh4 34. Rxh4 Rxh4 35. b4 cxb3 36. cxb3 Ke5 37.
Kd2 Rb4 38. Kc3 Rb8 39. Ra5 Kf4 40. Rb5 Rxb5 41. Bxb5 d4+ 42. Kxd4 Bxb3 43. Be8
f6 44. Bh5 Bd1 45. Kd5 Kg5 46. Bg4 f5 47. Bxf5 Kxf5 48. f4 Kxf4 1/2-1/2

