{in this game ..black played some...logical looking moves ..and soon he ended
up lost! ...black needs to know exactly what he is doing in this line!} 1. e4
e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Bc5 5. Nb3 Bb6 6. Nc3 d6 $6 7. Qe2 Bd7 $2 8.
Be3 $16 Bxe3 9. Qxe3 Nf6 10. O-O-O Qe7 11. f3 (11. Bb5 $5 a6 (11... O-O-O 12.
Bxc6 Bxc6 13. Qxa7) 12. Bxc6 Bxc6 13. f3 O-O (13... O-O-O 14. Qa7) 14. g4 $16
Rfe8 15. Nd4 (15. g5)) 11... O-O 12. g4 $18 {black has..absolutely no
counterplay ..and the a7-a5 advance is pointless !} h6 $2 (12... Be6 13. h4 a5
14. Nd4 $1 {ths is ..always the most simple against the a7-a5 advance.....
whenever Nb3-d4! is available, then a7-a5 is totally pointless!} (14. Bb5 $1
$18) 14... Nxd4 15. Qxd4 a4 16. a3 Rfd8 17. g5 Nh5 18. Qf2 $18) 13. h4 a5 14.
g5 hxg5 15. hxg5 Nh7 16. Nd5 Qxg5 17. f4 Qd8 18. Qg3 f5 19. Bc4 Be6 20. Rdg1
Qd7 21. Qh3 g5 22. Qh6 Kh8 23. Nf6 Rxf6 24. Qxf6+ Kg8 25. Rxg5+ Nxg5 26. Rh8#
1-0

